  "prompt": "What is the starting package for EE at IITB?",
  "response": "The **Electrical Engineering (EE)** program at **IIT Bombay** provides a strong foundation in electrical and electronics engineering concepts. While IIT Bombay does not explicitly mention a \"starting package,\" students in the EE program typically receive a **Placement Brochure** during their final year, which highlights their academic curriculum, technical skills, and areas of expertise to potential recruiters.\n\nDuring the placement season, EE graduates from IIT Bombay are highly sought after by top companies in sectors like software, core electrical, electronics, consulting, and finance. The **average salary package** for EE graduates at IIT Bombay is typically around **\u20b925\u201330 lakhs per annum (LPA)**, with some students receiving even higher offers, depending on their skills, internships, and project experience.\n\nFor more specific details about the starting package for EE students, you can refer to the **IIT Bombay Placements Report** or reach out to the **Career Development Cell (CDC)** at IIT Bombay.",
